    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>6 U.N. Soldiers Sent Home</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <dateline>UNITED NATIONS, Jan. 5</dateline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Six UN peacekeeping soldiers from Bangladesh have been sent home from Sudan after they were accused of committing sexual crimes (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Six United Nations peacekeeping soldiers have been sent home from duty in Sudan in recent months after they were investigated in connection with sexual crimes, officials here said Friday.</p>
        <p>The soldiers, who were from Bangladesh, were sent home after one of them was accused of sexually abusing of a Sudanese girl in June. The officials said that 13 allegations of sexual abuse involving peacekeepers in Sudan were currently under investigation.</p>
      </block>
